content: On August 26, 1995, the Atlanta Braves celebrated a significant milestone when they clinched the National League East title, marking their fourth consecutive division championship. The Braves secured the title with a 4-1 victory over the San Francisco Giants at Turner Field. This victory highlighted their dominance in the National League during the 1990s, setting the stage for a successful postseason run that would ultimately lead to the team's World Series championship that year.
